        "username": "yujian"
      },
      "date": "2017-05-30 16:39:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nHi James and Minh,\n\n> Hello Jian. Any plans to add ha.sh test to autotest system? Should we wait this? Or should I re-fresh the patch? Any chance that patch will be landed without autotest system modification to support it? Please advice.\n\nThe ha.sh was not written with the Lustre test framework, so it has not been supported by autotest system yet. I saw ATM-255 was created but it's still in backlog and might not be implemented in a short time.\n\nSo, IMHO, since the changes have been tested by Elena, \"testlist=ha\" can be removed from the test parameters to let the patch pass review testing and ready for land. What do you think about this?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "e9642a9289db218e2f24a6e91e7cd36389512c38",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 464,
